  "prompt": "What are the best side dishes for fried shrimp?",
  "response": "Fried shrimp pairs well with a variety of side dishes that complement its flavor and texture. Here are some of the best options:\n\n1. **Coleslaw** - A tangy, crunchy coleslaw adds a refreshing contrast to crispy fried shrimp.\n\n2. **French Fries** - Classic and always a favorite, crispy French fries are a perfect match for fried shrimp.\n\n3. **Hush Puppies** - These deep-fried cornmeal balls are a Southern favorite that goes well with seafood.\n\n4. **Corn on the Cob** - Sweet, buttery corn on the cob is a great addition to a shrimp meal, especially during summer.\n\n5. **Potato Salad** - Creamy potato salad offers a rich and satisfying complement to fried shrimp.\n\n6. **Fruit Salad** - A light fruit salad can provide a sweet and refreshing balance to the savory shrimp.\n\n7. **Grits** - Creamy or cheesy grits are a Southern staple that pairs wonderfully with shrimp.\n\n8. ** garlic bread** - Crunchy garlic bread can be a delicious accompaniment, adding richness to the meal.\n\n9. **Green Salad** - A simple mixed greens salad with a light vinaigrette can add a fresh element.\n\n10. **Macaroni and Cheese** - A classic comfort food, mac and cheese adds a creamy texture that many enjoy with shrimp.\n\n11. **Steamed Vegetables** - Lightly seasoned steamed veggies like asparagus or green beans provide a healthy balance.\n\n12. **Rice Pilaf** - Fluffy rice pilaf can absorb any sauces or juices from the shrimp, making it a great side.\n\nChoose one or a combination of these sides to create a delicious meal with fried shrimp!",
